<!-- ━━━ CHAPTER 2: The Risk Is Real ━━━ -->
<section class="slide slide--risk" id="risk">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="section-label reveal">Chapter 2</p>
    <h2 class="section-title reveal reveal-delay-1">The Risk Is Real</h2>

    <div class="risk-hero-quote reveal reveal-delay-2">
      <blockquote>
        An expired security certificate caused a six-hour outage to the Dynamic Red senate tracker &mdash; the real-time service used by parliamentarians, media, and the public to monitor daily Senate proceedings. The Department of Parliamentary Services revealed the certificate &ldquo;was issued from a different certificate authority, which wasn&rsquo;t documented and wasn&rsquo;t consistent with standard practices.&rdquo;
      </blockquote>
      <p class="incident-source">&mdash; iTnews, Australian Parliament, February 2026</p>
    </div>

    <div class="incident-grid">
      <div class="incident-card reveal reveal-delay-3">
        <strong>Google Bazel &mdash; Dec 2025</strong>
        <span>12-hour build outage on Christmas Day from an expired code-signing certificate</span>
      </div>
      <div class="incident-card reveal reveal-delay-4">
        <strong>Starlink &mdash; 2023</strong>
        <span>Expired ground station certificate disrupted satellite connectivity</span>
      </div>
      <div class="incident-card reveal reveal-delay-5">
        <strong>Ericsson / O2 &mdash; 2018</strong>
        <span>25 million users across 11 countries lost service for up to 24 hours</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="risk-stat reveal reveal-delay-6">
      <span class="counter-value" data-target="40" data-suffix="%">0%</span> of enterprises at risk
    </p>
    <p class="risk-stat-source reveal reveal-delay-7">&mdash; CSC Research, 2025</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ━━━ CHAPTER 3: Industry Shift — The 47-Day Era ━━━ -->
<section class="slide slide--shift" id="shift">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="section-label reveal">Chapter 3</p>
    <h2 class="section-title reveal reveal-delay-1">The 47-Day Era</h2>

    <p class="shift-lead reveal reveal-delay-2">
      The CA/Browser Forum adopted Apple's proposal &mdash; all major browsers voted in favour. The first reduction took effect March 2026. <strong>This is already happening.</strong>
    </p>

    <div class="timeline reveal reveal-delay-3">
      <div class="timeline-step past">
        <div class="marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-days">398</div>
        <div class="timeline-date">Before March 2026</div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-step active">
        <div class="marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-days">200</div>
        <div class="timeline-date">Now</div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-step future">
        <div class="marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-days">100</div>
        <div class="timeline-date">March 2027</div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-step future">
        <div class="marker"></div>
        <div class="timeline-days">47</div>
        <div class="timeline-date">March 2029</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="shift-callout reveal reveal-delay-4">
      <div class="callout-label">Key Insight</div>
      <div class="callout-text">Public CA standard today &mdash; internal CA best practice tomorrow.</div>
      <div class="callout-sub">This isn't just about public-facing certificates. When the industry standardises on short-lived certificates, the same expectation follows for internal systems &mdash; your private CA, your service mesh, your internal APIs. Here's what that looks like at scale for an organisation managing just 1,000 internal certificates:</div>
    </div>

    <div class="shift-stats">
      <div class="shift-stat-block reveal reveal-delay-5">
        <div class="big-number" style="color: var(--text-faint);">~1,825</div>
        <p><strong>Now (200-day max)</strong> &mdash; with 200-day lifetimes, ~5 certificates expire per day across a fleet of 1,000. That's ~1,825 renewals per year &mdash; already straining manual processes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="shift-stat-block reveal reveal-delay-6">
        <div class="big-number"><span class="counter-value" data-target="7700" data-suffix="+">0</span></div>
        <p><strong>By 2029</strong> &mdash; at 47-day lifetimes, that jumps to ~21 certificates expiring every single day. Over 7,700 renewals per year &mdash; an <strong>8&times; increase</strong>. No team can sustain that manually.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="shift-insight reveal reveal-delay-7">
      Manual processes cannot scale to 47-day cycles &mdash; automation becomes non-negotiable.
    </p>

    <p class="shift-source reveal reveal-delay-7">Source: CA/Browser Forum Ballot SC-081, April 2025</p>
  </div>
</section>

