      <div class="shield-layer">
        <span class="shield-num">Layer 01</span>
        <h3>Blast Radius Control</h3>
        <p>Canary deployments and rolling updates limit the impact of any certificate issue to a small subset of hosts before fleet-wide rollout.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="shield-layer">
        <span class="shield-num">Layer 02</span>
        <h3>Automatic Rollback</h3>
        <p>Health checks validate every deployment. On failure, Ansible restores the previous certificate automatically &mdash; no human intervention needed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="shield-layer">
        <span class="shield-num">Layer 03</span>
        <h3>Separation of Concerns</h3>
        <p>Vault owns trust and policy. AAP owns execution and orchestration. Neither can exceed its authority. Security and operations stay cleanly separated.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

